snippet.textDisplay: Should have called this 2 city boys trying to make a fire XD, look up primitive survival if you want to actually live in the woods. With the steel wool, you need to separate it a bit, and move the battery around, focusing on a bunch of the fibers, and have a tinder bundle ready to ignite, because you only need a small ember to make a fire. It can be vary challenging and requires patience to do, but this is fun to watch :P. Also not saying this in a "dumb city folk" way, no, why would you ever need to know how to do that, so it makes sense you wouldent know much about it. There are many things people who live in the country dont know about city life either, its cool to see people take a interest in something they could possibly use in the future. I think fire making is something everyone should know for survival reasons. It can be the difference between life and death if you get lost in the woods.
